column5: I had prior obligations with my mother tomorrow, but Paul is going to go piking up on Simcoe tomorrow and has room for 2 more if anyone is interested for a day of fishing in a beautiful Lund  He will be casting for them so you need a casting rod.  Anyone????
Sounds like fun.. but I'll be getting my "beautiful Lund" ready for Leah to tow North!!  Someone's gonna have fun.. tomorrow looks like a BEAUTY day !
Damn, damn, damn! I live too far away. If I left now I could make it but then I'd have to get back.
Generous offer. I'm in Montreal till tomorrow celebrating the day dedicated to the person who birthed me and am seriously jealous of those who will get to go.
Thats a very generous offer. If i wasnt in Haliburton, youd have one more Team member aboard! Good luck tomorrow.
Someone is very lucky. I have plans to spend time with the family.  I wish I was fishing lol.
Well whoever can go, it won't be all day, you'll make it home in time for dinner definately.  Probably until 2 p.m. or so.
Working Sunday really sucks  Good luck to whoever gets out.
IF YOU WANT TO FISH OUT OF A REAL NICE LUND,(BETTER THEN WAYNES    )TAKE UP THIS  NICE GENEROUS OFFER.  Im hopeing to get out in it, in the next couple of weeks.
Come on Roy , i can make sure you get back ...........
You got to be kidding me.......how can anyone turn down such a generous offer......
Hey I didn't turn it down, the decision was made for me!
The Gods hate me, owning your own business sucks, two jobs to do tomorrow. Damn , Damn, Damn would have been nice. Wanted to try out the new C3:
